<h1>Minty Frozen Chocolate Balls</h1>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
  <li>1/3 C cocoa powder</li>
  <li>1/3 C oat milk</li>
  <li>1/3 C maple syrup</li>
  <li>2 t vanilla extract</li>
  <li>1/4 t peppermint extract</li>
  <li>2 ripe bananas</li>
  <li>2 C oats</li>
  <li>1 C Grape-Nuts</li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
  <li>In a food processor, combine all but the oats and Grape-Nuts.</li>
  <li>Process until smooth and then transfer to a large bowl.</li>
  <li>Add the oats to the bowl and mix well.</li>
  <li>Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.</li>
  <li>Place Grape-Nuts in a small bowl.</li>
  <li>Using a melon baller or small spoon, scoop up wet, sticky chocolate balls and one by one drop them in the Grape-Nuts and roll them around to cover the surface of the ball.</li>
  <li>Place each ball on the parchment paper and flatten slightly with the back of a spoon.</li>
  <li>Freeze the balls.</li>
  <li>Serve frozen or just slightly thawed.</li>
</ol>
